storyInfo: Impassioned by Anita's warm enthusiasm, Skadi walks into the crowd of locals and begins to sing for them. The music manages to tug at the still heartstrings of the inhabitants, though this moment of peace is broken when the high tide signal is sounded.

attributes.text: The girl closes her eyes and lets go as she is told.

The force gripping onto her leg quickly disappears. She can hear all sorts of tiny trinkets splashing into the water. Just before she herself touches the surface of the sea, a force pulls her upward and sends her back to dry land again.

attributes.content: *cough* *cough* *cough*.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It's not easy to control the strength and angle while I'm dealing with a person.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I-It's okay. I'm fine.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: (Smells herself)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: My bleeding's stopped.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Why are they still so excited? Have there always been so many Sea Terrors here?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Are these the same monsters from last night?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: More or less.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I've never seen them before.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You should stay away from this place for a couple of days. Now go back.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Stop tugging my skirt... You aren't a child.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I just want to say... I think I know what it is that I want now. I want to hear you sing.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: And that's because... I don't know what songs are like. I heard you humming in your sleep, but I didn't understand it.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer, will you do it? Is this what it means to make a promise?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: More or less.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: (Frowns)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: My harp.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh? Oh yeah, singer, where did your harp go?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'll go look for it...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Okay. I'll help.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: So does this mean you'll come back with me? G-Great!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Is this something to be so happy about?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hey, Drywall, good morning!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Sheetmetal...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Oh yeah, where did Sheetmetal go? You never go anywhere without each other.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Sheetmetal.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Are you looking out... to the sea?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Does this mean... It was Sheetmetal who got the red seashell last night?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Woodframe, my condition got worse.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: My chest is bloating like it's about to blow.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: I don't even want to eat. Leave me alone.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: *Sigh*...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, welcome to our home sweet home again!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Ugh... agh...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Your grandmother...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Grandma Petra is still sleeping. She's been lying down ever since we got back last night.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She's probably tired, getting so worked up like that. I didn't expect her to run out and talk to the Inquisitor like that. She was different.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're right. That was very amazing. She fought off the Inquisitor.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hmn... ha...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: She fought off.. the Inquisitor?! Singer, if the Inquisitor catches you saying that, she'll be really mad.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I don't care if she does.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: But if she wants another go...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She won't come to you looking for trouble again, right?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It doesn't matter to me whose trouble she's looking for.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: (Strokes case)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Oh, yeah, why don't we go look for your harp?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Hold on.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Eh?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You got stuff on your head.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Whoa! All this green, slimy stuff... W-What is this?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: That's seaweed.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Did it get on my head when I tripped?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Probably.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Is this stuff... useful in any way? Looks kinda like seagrass. Can I use it as bedding once it's dried? Grandma Petra's back is hurting her, so this will come in handy.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Give it to me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Take some seashells and use them to grind up these seaweeds. Don't wash off the slime.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Add enough seawater to completely cover the seaweeds. Put it all in a jar and seal it up, then wait half a year.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You can drink it once the liquid's greenish color has faded. That's when it's fermented.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer...?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What's wrong? Is there something you didn't understand?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: No... I just don't think you've ever talked to me this much in one go.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Don't throw away your seashells either. Wash them and lay them out to dry. You can use them to drink alcohol and such.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Alcohol? What's that?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It's written right there. This place used to be a bar, a place for alcohol.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: So this word means alcohol!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Alcohol can supposedly bring happiness and help us forget all our worries.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Does it work?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Not at all...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It does taste pretty good, though.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Did you drink this stuff often back home...? Back in Ægir?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Not exactly.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I would drink something similar before dances.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It must have been very fun. Oh, I get it now! Alcohol doesn't bring happiness, but we drink alcohol when we're happy!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Does everyone outside, uh, drink alcohol? Is everyone out there always so happy?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Not necessarily.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: I get it. They definitely aren't as happy as I am now. Singer, thanks for teaching me how to make alcohol. I really wanna drink it with you right now.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Your hand movement is wrong.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: If you grind it like that, it's not going to grind up very well. Try a different angle. Use the sharpest point and follow the seaweed's pattern.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Control your rhythm and your breathing... Make your hand and your whole body one with the sea breeze that's brushing against your skin.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Like that—One stroke, and it's shredded.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You are staring at me. Do you still want another go? Now that there's only one of you, it'll be over very quickly.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: No... I don't think I will.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: This is yours.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Hmm?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: This is my harp.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Sheetmetal found it.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: He saw you drop it outside last night.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Oh, that's great! Singer, now we don't need to go look for your harp!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: He brought it back to our house... and... and he told me to give it to you.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: That's all he said before he left...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Thanks.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh? Oh...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: (Plucks strings)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Huh...? This melody... You were humming it while you were asleep last night.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: It's always in my head.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Is this a song that you and your partner used to sing?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: We have a lot of songs like this back home. We sing... as a way to talk to each other.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: When I left, the singing was gone too. I'm all by myself, and this song is all that I have left.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: No wonder this song sounds so sad.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: (Plucks strings)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Singer, remember our promise?! You got your harp back. Does that mean you can sing for us now?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: We're all waiting. Right, Grandma Petra?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Mmn... Uhh...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Grandma probably can't talk today. She would sing along with you if she could.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Ah... Ahhh...
attributes.name: Old Inhabitant

attributes.content: Singer, Grandma wants to hear your song.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.text: Clad in her red dress, the wandering singer sits in the middle of the group. She closes her eyes as her fingers stroke the strings of her harp.

The notes and the lyrics flow out from her naturally as she plunks away at her harp strings, permeating every corner of the rundown bar. The melody twists and expands in the air as though this is where it belongs.

attributes.content: A hunter is walking on seacoast way♪
With homeland left a mile behind, his path lies ahead♪
From his forebears and children, he was torn♪
Into the seas his lover was swept away, floating in the deep, dead♪
I noticed a change in your expression. Did you feel something, perhaps?
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Nothing.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: Not a surprise. Your reflexes are still rather slow. Look at the water before you. The fluctuation of the level, the frequency of the waves, and the movement of its luster. All of these are information.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: It'll be high tide soon. We should go.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: A hunter is walking on seacoast way♪
With homeland left a mile behind, they must lament and pray♪
There is no end to his path♪
The road ahead is shrouded in gray♪
She's singing.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: How could she sing in front of these people in this rundown house?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: And... they are listening to her.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The ones who hang their heads are still looking straight at the floor. The ones who don't speak are still silent as ever. Her singing has no way to reach their cold, hard husks, but their eyes...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Do they understand it somehow?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: A hunter is walking on seacoast way♪
The singer stops her fingers, but the harmony formed by her harp and voice together does not simply disappear because of that.
It yet remains with the wanderer herself, creating an open seam in the thick dust.
A few sprouts land in that crevice just as others begin to sprout from it.

attributes.content: Grandma Petra?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What's wrong?
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: She... fell asleep.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: She never sleeps so peacefully. Most of the time, she starts screaming the moment she closes her eyes, grasping at nothing.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I thought she'd want to dance when she heard you sing. I mean, she's always chirping about how she wants to dance.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Drywall?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'm going to die. There's seawater in my eyes... It's salty. Not tasty at all.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Whoa... Are you... crying?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Crying? What is that?
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: It's a kind of emotion that flows out from the deepest depths of your body...
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It is...? I don't think I understand.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Singer, I like your songs. You don't like to talk, but you have so much to tell when you are singing.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Could you sing it again? I want to hear you talk about lots more.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: (Plucks strings)
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.text: The sea breeze envelops the singer's fingers and wafts into her nostrils. The smell here has changed.

attributes.content: Food...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: We'll have food again...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: To the beach.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: Priest!
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.text: The melody of her song has stopped.
